== Enchilada Chicken ==

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with
half the @Southwest spice blend{1/2%tablespoon}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @tomato paste{1.5%ounce}, @Tex-Mex paste{1},
and @water{1/4%cup}.

Transfer chicken and sauce to 1 #oven-ready aluminum tray{} (divide between 2 trays for 4); flip chicken to coat both sides.

Roast on middle rack until chicken is cooked through, ~{22-28%minutes}.

== Southwest Rice & Beans ==

Meanwhile, gently massage @microwavable rice{1} in package to break up grains,
then transfer to a #medium bowl{}.

Drain @black beans{13.4%ounce can}, reserving 1 TBSP liquid (2 TBSP for
4 servings), then rinse.

To bowl with rice, stir in beans, reserved bean liquid, @chili powder{1%tsp},
remaining Southwest spice, @salt{3/4%tsp} (1 1/2 tsp for 4), and pepper.

Transfer to remaining #oven-ready aluminum tray{} (remaining 2 trays for 4). Top
with @butter{3%tablespoon} and cover tightly with #foil{}.

Bake on middle rack until warmed through and butter has melted, ~{20-22%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Once chicken is cooked through, remove all trays from oven and heat broiler
to high. Top chicken with @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}.

Return tray with chicken to middle rack until cheese is melted and lightly
browned, ~{2-3%minutes}. Let cool slightly.

Fluff rice and beans with a #fork{}; stir to incorporate butter and season with
@salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Divide between plates and top with cheesy chicken. Drizzle with
@smoky red pepper crema{4%tablespoon} and as much @hot sauce{1%tsp} as you
like. Serve.